SIMPLE: mediation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mediation
<hw>Me`di*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>mediacioun</ets>, F. <ets>m⟦eacute⟧diation</ets>. See
<er>Mediate</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
mediating; action or relation of anything interposed; action as a
necessary condition, means, or instrument; interposition;
intervention.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The soul [acts] by the <qex>mediation</qex> of these passions.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, specifically, agency between parties at
variance, with a view to reconcile them; entreaty for another;
intercession.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mediative</ent>⟦br⟧
